race.description: Sportsbet Nobody Does It Better Hcp (60)
race.comment: ONE KIND (10) was in the mix at Morphettville before fading late, but this is a softer target and he's on the quick back-up. Expect a sharp bounce back. GUSMAO (13) arrives off a nose win at Balaklava and boasts a solid record at this trip. He's consistent, fit, and rates a genuine winning chance again. VALLENCOURT (6) didn't fire last time but was in striking range and now finds a more suitable race. Capable of turning things around. MIDNIGHT RULER (2) returns and is tricky to catch but has best figures to threaten. Wide draw hurts but Murtagh's booking is a plus. PRESCIENT (8) closed last prep in good order and is proven over this journey. Include.
